This is my first contact to assembler code, focused on the motorola 6809, a 16bits processor.

Once the program is executed an option menu will be printed, giving 6 options

 ============================================
 |                                          |
 | (1) INTRODUCIR MATRICES                  |  Introduce matrix will ask for two 3x3 matrix               
 | (2) MOSTRAR MATRICES                     |  Show matrix
 | (3) MULTIPLICAR FILAS                    |  Multiplies each of the elements of a row
 | (4) SUMAR Y CALCULAR MEDIA DE FILAS      |  It will add every element of each row and show the average value
 | (5) MULTIPLICAR MATRICES                 |  Multiplies the two matrix
 | (6) SALIR                                |  Exits the program
 |                                          |
 ============================================   
 
Each of the options and the output of the menu are programmed in diferent subroutines, except for exit which is already in the main 
code.

To build and run this program you will have to install asm6809 emulator or any other for the 6809

This are the instructions:

1-) as6809 -l -o _____.asm     

	Do this for every single .asm in the folder and for each one a .rel is going to be created 
	
2-) aslink -s -m -w final.s19 xxxx.rel
	
	Add every .rel that has been generated to the instruction     

3-) m6809-run final.s19 (Add a -d in the middle in case you want to enter debugger mode)

	Runs the program
	



